<div class="devlog_entry">
    <h1>Mar 17 2026: Small Steps</h1>
    <hr>
    <p> Today I contacted a representative for an apprenticeship
        involving full-stack development, but it is covered in
        red flags. After the contact responded with the details
        of the apprenticeship, I noticed vague wording regarding
        the subjects they teach. It is clearly structured as
        a class, which is perfectly fine, until you see its outrageous
        pricing. I originally figured this was an "earn and learn"
        program, but I was horribly wrong. Regardless, I added some CSS
        to this website, allowing each devlog to fill its own bubble.
        Soon I will store devlogs in a separate document and present
        them on the page dynamically ... after I learn how. Until next time,
        thank you for reading my second devlog. Goodbye for now.
    </p>
